import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    business_counts = data['key'].value_counts()
    ax = sns.barplot(x=business_counts.index, y=business_counts.values)
    ax.set_xlabel('Business Type')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of business types in the University District?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    # Calculate distances between businesses
    distances = []
    for i in range(len(data) - 1):
        lat1, lat2 = data['lat'].iloc[i], data['lat'].iloc[i + 1]
        distance = np.abs(lat2 - lat1)
        distances.append(distance)
    
    # Plot histogram of distances
    sns.histplot(distances, kde=False, bins=20)
    
    # Calculate average distance
    avg_distance = np.mean(distances)
    
    # Add vertical line for average distance
    plt.axvline(avg_distance, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {avg_distance:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    
    # Set x-axis ticks
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the average distance between businesses in the University District?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
